B.Pm=new A.aE("b_dart_1","dart_fundamentals","Types",B.az,B.A,"What is the difference between var, final, and const in Dart?","var allows reassignment and type inference. final allows single assignment at runtime. const is a compile-time constant that is deeply immutable.","var x = 1; x = 2; // OK\nfinal y = DateTime.now(); // set once at runtime\nconst z = 3.14; // must be known at compile time\n\nconst also makes the value deeply immutable \u2014 a const List cannot have items added to it.",null,null)
B.Pu=new A.aE("b_dart_2","dart_fundamentals","Null Safety",B.az,B.A,"What is null safety in Dart and why is it important?","Null safety means variables are non-nullable by default. You must explicitly mark a type as nullable with ? (e.g., String?). This prevents null reference errors at compile time.","Before null safety, any variable could be null, causing runtime crashes. With sound null safety, the compiler guarantees non-nullable variables always have a value.",null,null)
B.P5=new A.aE("b_dart_3","dart_fundamentals","Async/Await",B.az,B.A,"What is the difference between Future and Stream in Dart?","A Future represents a single asynchronous value that completes once. A Stream represents a sequence of asynchronous values over time.","Future<String> is like a Promise \u2014 it resolves once. Stream<String> emits multiple values, like a subscription to data (e.g., Firestore snapshots, WebSocket messages).",null,null)
